{"id":14779,"date":"2019-06-21T22:03:23","date_gmt":"2019-06-21T21:03:23","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/?p=14779"},"modified":"2022-09-20T13:08:28","modified_gmt":"2022-09-20T11:08:28","slug":"istanbul-balat","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/turkey\/istanbul-balat\/","title":{"rendered":"Istanbul\u2019s Must-See: The Colorful Houses of Balat"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2>About Balat, Istanbul<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Balat is one of the oldest districts of Istanbul with some wooden houses over 200 years old. Friendly local families, a cultural mix of Jewish, Christians, and Muslims people are all welcoming you to their neighborhood. Balat has Synagogues, Churches, and Mosques, something you don&#x2019;t see all along that often. The second you enter Balat with its colorful historical buildings and narrow streets, you will forget that you&#x2019;re in <a aria-label=\"Turkey (opens in a new tab)\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/turkey\/\">Turkey<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--attractions \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--attractions\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><strong>Best of Istanbul?<\/strong> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/best-of-istanbul-tour\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Join the popular Istanbul tour.<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/d